content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1271.11 - Starting and warm-ups restricted to designated areas

State Regulations

Aircraft engines shall be started and warmed up on the
air terminal only in places designated for such purposes by the manager. No jet
or turbo-prop aircraft engine shall be run-up except on warm-up pads or in
other areas authorized for that purpose by the manager. Notes
